    "BRITON ADVISES US TO BUILD CRUISERS Future Will Take Care of It i self He Says Commenting on Borah Proposal BY FREDERIC WILLIAM WILE Build your 15 cruisers lake the British propaganda complex out of American naval discussion and the fu tureincluding freedom of the seas will take care of itself Thus spoke to the writer a distinguished Briton in Washington who was asked to com ment on Senator Borahs proposal to defer the construction of American cruisers until there has been an at tempt to recodify maritime law at an International conference The person quoted is in position to reflect au tnoritative British opinion The Summer or Fall of 1929 when administrations will be in office at feoth Washington and London is named as the moment when AngloAmerican Raval questions ought to be approach able from a fresh angle President Hoovers regime will not have been in stalled very long before the British general elections will take place It Ls well within the range of possibilities that the naval issue may figure con spicuously in the parliamentary cam paign which will be fought out in May June or July According to the present outlook the existing Baldwin Conservative government"
